theorem dense_left_and_P2_right_implies_P2_prod
    {X Y : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] [TopologicalSpace Y]
    {A : Set X} {B : Set Y} :
    Dense A → Topology.P2 B → Topology.P2 (A ×ˢ B) := by
  intro hDense hP2B
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at hP2B ⊢
  intro p hp
  -- Coordinates of the point `p`
  have hpA : p.1 ∈ A := hp.1
  have hpB : p.2 ∈ B := hp.2
  -- Apply `P2` to the second coordinate
  have hIntB : p.2 ∈ interior (closure (interior B)) := hP2B hpB
  -- Thanks to the density of `A`, the following interior is the whole space
  have hUnivA :
      interior (closure (interior A)) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    interior_closure_interior_eq_univ_of_dense (X := X) (A := A) hDense
  -- Assemble the membership in the product of interiors
  have hMemProd : (p : X × Y) ∈
      interior (closure (interior A)) ×ˢ
        interior (closure (interior B)) := by
    have hp1 : p.1 ∈ interior (closure (interior A)) := by
      have : p.1 ∈ (Set.univ : Set X) := by
        trivial
      simpa [hUnivA] using this
    exact And.intro hp1 hIntB
  -- Identify the target interior set for the product
  have hEq :=
    interior_closure_interior_prod (X := X) (Y := Y) (A := A) (B := B)
  -- Conclude the desired membership
  simpa [hEq] using hMemProd
